{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17565638","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17565638"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T23:29:56+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T23:29:56+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17836"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}},{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17640563","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17640563"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T19:18:14+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T19:18:14+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17836"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"17836","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/17836"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.01,0.05,0.93,0.01,0.01]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10550"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"73245"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"10550","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/10550"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17836"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"58716"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"17"},{"type":"tags","id":"18"},{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"5326"},{"type":"tags","id":"5631"},{"type":"tags","id":"5652"},{"type":"tags","id":"5764"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"24594"},{"type":"contributions","id":"25015"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"73245","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/73245"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EThe Human Tissue Act governs the removal, storage, use, and disposal of human tissue in Australia. This legislation was introduced to ensure ethical handling of human tissue and to protect individual autonomy.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes the consent requirements for storing human tissue for educational purposes?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Consent is not required for educational use of tissue","Consent is implied if tissue is obtained during routine procedures","Explicit consent is required from the person or their nominated representative","Consent from any family member is sufficient","Consent is only required for genetic research"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe correct answer is that \u003Cstrong\u003Eexplicit consent is required from the person or their nominated representative\u003C/strong\u003E. The Human Tissue Act mandates that specific consent must be obtained for the storage and use of human tissue for purposes beyond immediate clinical care, including education and research.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EConsent is not required for educational use of tissue\u003C/strong\u003E is incorrect because all educational use of tissue requires explicit consent under the Human Tissue Act.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EConsent is implied if tissue is obtained during routine procedures\u003C/strong\u003E is incorrect because separate explicit consent is required for any use beyond immediate clinical care, even for routine samples.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EConsent from any family member is sufficient\u003C/strong\u003E is incorrect because only the person themselves or their legally nominated representative can provide valid consent under the Act.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EConsent is only required for genetic research\u003C/strong\u003E is incorrect because consent requirements apply to all forms of tissue storage and use, not just genetic research.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThis legislation ensures that individuals maintain autonomy over their tissue samples and that proper ethical standards are maintained in medical education and research.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["The Human Tissue Act requires explicit consent for the storage and use of human tissue for research, education, and training purposes.","Consent for tissue storage must be obtained from the person while living or from their nominated representative after death.","Tissue samples taken during diagnostic procedures require separate consent for storage and use beyond diagnosis."],"references":["Ethical and Legal Issues in Relation to the Use of Human Tissue in Australia and New Zealand. Royal College of Pathologists Australia (RCPA). Updated August 2022. Available from: https://www.rcpa.edu.au/getattachment/ad0d4af1-901a-4056-af05-56bbc06167c1/Ethical-and-Legal-Issues-in-Relation-to-the-Use-of.aspx"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"58716"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17836"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"58716","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/58716"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-23T09:43:54+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-23T09:44:19+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10550"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"73245"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"17","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/17"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\ude07